<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="368" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1388,1955]" pageId="1" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1712,1738]" pageId="1" pageNumber="368">Remarks.</emphasis>
The first record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1928" box="[535,629,1712,1738]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampithoidae" genus="Grubia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="368" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="filosa">
<emphasis box="[535,629,1712,1738]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="368">C. filosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Persian Gulf is referred by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jones, D. A." box="[1012,1156,1712,1739]" pageId="1" pageNumber="368" refId="ref4893" refString="Jones, D. A. (1986) A Field Guide to the Sea Shores of Kuwait and the Arabian Gulf. Universty of Kuwait, Distributed Blandford Press, Kuwait City, 192 pp." type="book" year="1986">Jones (1986)</bibRefCitation>
from the 
<collectingCountry box="[1267,1349,1712,1738]" name="Kuwait" pageId="1" pageNumber="368">Kuwait</collectingCountry>
waters, which was recently reported by Myers &amp; Nithindaranan (2016) from the 
<collectingCountry box="[985,1067,1748,1774]" name="Kuwait" pageId="1" pageNumber="368">Kuwait</collectingCountry>
coasts. They mentioned that the material agrees well with the Mediterranean material that was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Peart, R. A." box="[988,1130,1784,1811]" pageId="1" pageNumber="368" pagination="301 - 336" refId="ref5828" refString="Peart, R. A. (2004) A revision of the Cymadusa filosa complex (Crustacea: Amphipoda: Corophioidea: Ampithoidae). Journal of Natural History, 38, 301 - 336. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 0022293021000055441" type="journal article" year="2004">Peart (2004)</bibRefCitation>
. The material of the present study from the northern coasts of the Persian Gulf differs in some characters. The third article of mandibular palp is the longest in the Persian Gulf material, but in 
<bibRefCitation author="Peart, R. A." box="[672,830,1856,1882]" pageId="1" pageNumber="368" pagination="301 - 336" refId="ref5828" refString="Peart, R. A. (2004) A revision of the Cymadusa filosa complex (Crustacea: Amphipoda: Corophioidea: Ampithoidae). Journal of Natural History, 38, 301 - 336. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 0022293021000055441" type="journal article" year="2004">Peart’s (2004)</bibRefCitation>
studied material the second article is the longest. Also the first coxa in the present material is produced anteriorly and the dactylus in second male gnathopod is shorter, not reaching the end of palm. The present studied material was collected from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. Adanson" authorityYear="1763" box="[988,1069,1928,1954]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Dictyotaceae" genus="Padina" kingdom="Chromista" order="Dictyotales" pageId="1" pageNumber="368" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[988,1069,1928,1954]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="368">Padina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
algae on silky cover.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
